content: Hi Sarah! I'm interested in your heirloom tomatoes. Do you have any available for pickup this weekend?
Hi Mike! Yes, I have plenty of heirloom tomatoes available. You can come by Saturday morning between 9-11 AM. The farm is located at 123 Green Valley Road.
Perfect! I'll be there around 10 AM. Should I bring cash or do you accept cards?
Both cash and cards work fine! Looking forward to seeing you. Feel free to walk around the farm and see our other produce too.
Hi Michael! I'm interested in your fresh milk. Do you deliver to the downtown area?
Hi Jennifer! Yes, we deliver to downtown on Tuesdays and Fridays. What size would you like? We have half-gallon and gallon bottles.
Hello David! I'd like to visit your orchard for apple picking. What are your hours this weekend?
Hi Alex! We're open Saturday 9 AM - 5 PM and Sunday 10 AM - 4 PM. The Honeycrisp apples are at their peak right now!
Hi Linda! Are your strawberries still in season? I'd love to bring my kids for u-pick!
Hi Sophia! Yes, strawberries are still going strong! We're open for u-pick on weekends 8 AM - 2 PM. The kids will love it!
Hello Robert! I'm a baker and interested in your whole wheat flour. Do you have any bulk pricing?
Hi James! Yes, we offer 10% discount on orders over 50 lbs. The flour is stone-ground fresh weekly. How much are you looking for?
Hi Maria! I'm interested in your microgreens for my restaurant. Do you offer regular delivery?
Hi Emma! Yes, we deliver to restaurants twice weekly. What's your restaurant name and how much volume do you need?
Hi Sarah! I loved the goat cheese I bought last week. Do you have any more available?
Hi William! I'm so glad you enjoyed it! Yes, I have 8 wheels left from this week's batch. They're aged to perfection!
Hi Michael! I'm interested in your aged cheddar. How long has it been aged?
Hi Olivia! The cheddar is aged for 12 months. It has a nice sharp flavor that's perfect for cheese boards or cooking. Would you like to try a sample?
Hi David! I'm planning to make apple cider donuts. Which apple variety would you recommend?
Hi Mike! For cider donuts, I'd recommend the Northern Spy apples - they have the perfect tartness and hold their shape well when cooked. We have plenty in stock!
Hi Linda! I'm making a mixed berry pie. Do you have raspberries and blueberries available?
Hi Jennifer! Yes, both are in season and looking beautiful! The raspberries are especially sweet right now. How many pints do you need?
